The woman, who is known to the baby's family, allegedly snatched little Lucas Cedras on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - A Kraaifontein woman faces criminal charges for allegedly abducting an eight-month-old baby.The suspect was arrested outside her Scottsdene home on Friday following appeals by the police for the community's assistance in their investigation.The woman, who is known to the baby's family, allegedly snatched little Lucas Cedras on Tuesday.It's been reported the child's grandmother allowed the woman to take him for a while, but she never returned.The police's Fredrick van Wyk says: The 37-year-old suspect was arrested in Scottsdene on Friday. She will appear in the Kuils River Magistrates Court on 16 January. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)